<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It is unfortunate that you choose this deceptive tactic to libel a book about truthfulness. Ironic, isn&apos;t it. Please click on some of the people who r<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It is unfortunate that you choose this deceptive tactic to libel a book about truthfulness. Ironic, isn't it. Please click on some of the people who reviewed the book and you'll see that many have extensive Goodreads histories with a wide variety of reviews. For example, here's one <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/61116208-alison-evans">https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/6...</a><br /><br />And here's another <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/90210186-stephan-lewandowsky">https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/9...</a><br /><br />But what do you care about the facts if you just want to bash a book about truthfulness, right? Facts won't sway you, it's not how post-truth double-speak works. I won't engage any more on this topic. Goodbye. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
